10 A Concurrent Resolution urging Oklahoma's
Congressional Delegation to support the Credit for
11 Caring Act for family caregivers.
12
13
14 WHEREAS, family caregivers play a vital role in supporting loved
15 ones with long-term health needs, often bearing significant
16 financial and emotional burdens as they provide essential care; and
17 WHEREAS, the Credit for Caring Act seeks to provide a federal
18 tax credit of up to $5,000 annually to working family caregivers,
19 helping to offset the high costs of caregiving and alleviating
20 financial strain; and
21 WHEREAS, Oklahoma is home to an estimated 490,000 family
22 caregivers who collectively contribute over $6.6 billion in unpaid
23 care, providing critical support that allows many older Oklahomans
24
